main event: A UFO was observed by Air Force personnel at Whiteman AFB, Missouri on May 5, 1963.
interesting points: The UFO was observed visually by three Whiteman AFB tower operators, as well as by the pilots of a T-33 aircraft.
The UFO was described as circular, the size of a 'head of a pin', and white or light orange in color.
The UFO was stationary for approximately 5 minutes before climbing at a high speed on a southerly course.
The sighting lasted for a total of 6 minutes.
The Air Force Intelligence officer evaluated the sighting as likely being a balloon, but the reliability of the observers was considered good to excellent.
sighted object: a circular, white or light orange UFO
witnesses: 3 Whiteman AFB tower operators, and the pilots of a T-33 aircraft
